                Secretary of Education Betsy DeVos has <a href="update:%20Department%20of%20Education%20(ED)%20•%20NEW:%20On%20April%2022,%20Secretary%20of%20Education%20Betsy%20DeVos%20called%20on%20wealthy%20institutions,%20or%20those%20with%20large%20endowments,%20to%20forgo%20federal%20emergency%20grant%20support%20and%20urged%20Congress%20to%20restrict%20taxpayer%20funds%20from%20wealthy%20institutions%20to%20make%20sure%20no%20more%20taxpayer%20funds%20go%20to%20elite,%20wealthy%20institutions.%20Secretary%20DeVos’%20statement%20is%20available%20at%20https://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/secretary-devos-calls-wealthy-institutions-reject-taxpayer-emergency-funds-congress-change-eligibility.">called on</a> wealthy institutions, or those with large endowments, to forgo federal emergency grant support and urged Congress to restrict taxpayer funds going to  wealthy institutions.
