                NEA has posted the agency’s CARES Act funded grant competition to help arts organizations endure financial impacts from COVID-19. NEA received $75 million through the CARES Act. Applicants must be previous NEA awardees from the past four years. Applications are due April 22 via the grants.gov portal and must also be submitted to the Endowment’s application portal between April 27<sup>th</sup> and May 4<sup>th</sup>. Details on this program can be found <a href="https://www.arts.gov/grants-organizations/CARES/grant-program-description">here</a>.
