                Rolling through April 14, 2021
              </td>
                                                                  <td>
                To improve understanding of the neurological consequences of infection of SARS-CoV-2 and of COVID-19, addressing the biology, pathophysiology, prevention, diagnosis, sequelae, or treatment of the 2019 Novel Coronavirus on neurological systems.
              </td>
